strings: <voice_0x01001017><se_def>Dhoulmagus: Aaaaaaargh!
<voice_0x01001018><se_def>Dhoulmagus: ...No! Not now! It cannot end now...
<voice_0x01001019><se_low>Yangus: We done it, guv! We finally given that Dhoulmagus wot 'e 'ad comin'!
<voice_0x0100101A><se_low>Yangus: He 'ad us goin' all round the 'ouses, eh!

<voice_0x0100101B><se_low>Yangus: I bet the old codger and the 'orse-princess
are back to normal now.
They'll be 'avin' a right old time!

<voice_0x0100101C><se_def>Angelo: Now Abbot Francisco can rest in peace.
And I'm free to do as I please!
<voice_0x0100101D><se_def>Angelo: How about you, Jessica? Feeling better now Dhoulmagus has got his come-uppance?

<voice_0x0100101E><se_def>Angelo: Hm? What's wrong? You can tell me.
I'm a good listener.
<voice_0x0100101F><se_high>Jessica: Defeating Dhoulmagus isn't going to bring Alistair back. It's hard to know what to feel...
<voice_0x01001020><se_low>*: Yoo-hoo!

<voice_0x01001021><se_low>Yangus: Ah! Grandad!
Finally transmorfed back to an 'uman, eh!

<voice_0x01001022><se_low>Yangus: Hang on, Grandad!
You still look like a freak!

<voice_0x01001023><se_low>King Trode: I AM NOT YOUR GRANDAD!
And if you must make fun of someone,
perhaps you should look in a mirror!

<voice_0x01001024><se_def>Angelo: He wasn't making fun of you.
We've just defeated Dhoulmagus.
You and the Princess should be back to normal.
<voice_0x01001025><se_low>King Trode: You defeated Dhoulmagus!? But this can't be! Why on earth hasn't the curse been lifted?
<voice_0x01001026><se_low>King Trode: Oh, no, no, no!
<voice_0x01001027><se_low>King Trode: ...Why? Why isn't it wearing off!?

<voice_0x01001028><se_low>King Trode: Ever since he stole the treasured sceptre from
my castle...

<voice_0x01001029><se_low>King Trode: Ah-ha! Yes! What about the sceptre!?
What's happened to it?
<voice_0x0100102A><se_high>Jessica: You mean this?
<voice_0x0100102B><se_low>King Trode: Yes! That's it! My family's treasured sceptre!

<voice_0x0100102C><se_low>Yangus: Oi, Grandad.
Hadn't we better be gettin' out of 'ere soon?
<voice_0x0100102D><se_low>King Trode: Hm! I suppose you're right. We won't accomplish anything twiddling our thumbs here.
<voice_0x0100102E><se_low>King Trode: Let's go back to Argonia for a while.
